Tip","text":"<p>Create simple sophistication or vibrancy with your logo by using a <em>handmade style.<\/em> Hand-drawn lines are perfect for businesses that want to convey a sense of tradition, quality, and authenticity.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Choose your logotype.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Now that you've determined the style of your logo, you need to decide on the type of logo that's most appropriate for your business. There are <a href=\"https:\/\/www.zarla.com\/guides\/types-of-logos\">seven different logotypes<\/a> to choose from:<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-make-a-logo#how-to-make-a-logo-section2-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-choose-your-logotype-288x288-20210826-1.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>A <em>monogram<\/em> or <em>lettermark<\/em> typically consists of two or three letters that can be accompanied by a graphic, but typically stands alone. The initials of the brand name are commonly used in a monogram. Some examples include NASA, H&amp;M, and BBC.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Sometimes called symbolic or iconic logos, <em>pictorial marks<\/em> are logos comprising distinct images without text. These logos typically use one or two colors but are easily identifiable without any color. The Nike swoosh and Twitter mascot, Larry the Bird, are some examples.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Also called logotypes, <em>wordmarks<\/em> use the full name of the brand or company as the logo. A unique font and a distinctive name create a good wordmark. Focus on typography, font, and color when designing a wordmark. Some examples include Coca-Cola, VISA, and Disney.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>An easy way to create an approachable brand is by using a <em>mascot logo.<\/em> These logos use characters as their focal points, which help to build rapport between the brand and the audience. These logos are frequently accompanied by brand names, but a really good mascot should be able to stand on its own.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>If you're looking to create a logo that carries prestige and status, opt for an <em>emblem logo.<\/em> These comprise icons or symbols with textual elements inside them. Think of a school badge. These logotypes are favored by organizations, institutions, and government agencies.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p><em>Abstract logos<\/em> offer unique, unlimited design options and retain their relevance even when the nature of the company changes. These logos have no intrinsic connection to your brand.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>If none of the above appeal to you, a <em>combination mark<\/em> may be the answer. Combination logos use both text and graphics \u2014 icons, mascots, or symbols \u2014 to represent a brand. Both text and visual elements should exist in harmony within the logo.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Before committing to a single logo design, try out a few options and see what works best.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Wordmarks and combination marks are better suited to new businesses that are not yet established, as they contain the name and\/or an image and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.zarla.com\/guides\/what-is-a-slogan\">slogan<\/a> of the business.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Consider logo variations for your brand.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Because your logo will invariably appear in several different spaces, having multiple versions of it will make it easier to integrate across platforms and to display on promotional products. A logo variation is essentially your main logo, just in a slightly different format.<\/p>\n<p>No matter where your logo's going to appear, choose from the following logo variations for the perfect fit.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-make-a-logo#how-to-make-a-logo-section2-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-consider-logo-variations-for-your-brand-288x288-20210826-2.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>The <em>primary logo<\/em> is your main logo from which all other variations are created. This logo comprises your business name, slogan, graphics, and brand colors. This logo is typically visible in your store, on your website, and other marketing materials.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>The elements of your primary logo can be rearranged to create a <em>secondary logo.<\/em> The easiest way to do this is to switch the orientation from stacked to horizontal, or vice versa. A secondary logo may be found on labels, other printed materials, and social media branding.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>The simplified version of your logo, better known as a <em>submark<\/em> or <em>brandmark<\/em>, includes the full brand name and a small icon. In some cases, submarks may use the initials of your business name. These can be found in small spaces, such as footers on websites or emails, business cards, blog graphics, and more.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>If you have an icon in your main logo, you can use this on its own as a <em>brand element<\/em>. The initials of your business name can also be turned into an icon that represents your business. Brand elements can be replicated to produce patterns on your website, or they can be used as favicons, adding a perfect finishing touch to your website.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"4","name":"<p>Use the right colors to convey meaning.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Color plays a crucial role in marketing and advertising. By choosing the right <a href=\"https:\/\/www.zarla.com\/guides\/logo-colors\">colors for your logo<\/a>, you can expand your brand narrative and evoke certain feelings and ideas you want your brand associated with.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-make-a-logo#how-to-make-a-logo-section2-step4","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-ponle-color-288x288-20210816.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Make a note of the colors your competitors and other top brands have used in their logos.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Test various color combinations and shades until you find the best color scheme for your logo.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Combining colors can be tricky, so get some input from others before making a final decision.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>When it comes to logo designs, keep it simple. Create a logo that's easy to replicate, comprises one to three colors, and is recognizable even in plain black.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"5","name":"<p>Be mindful of font, typeface, and typography.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>The typeface, font, and typography (arrangement of letters within your logo) all play a vital role in the appearance and overall appeal of your logo, so you'll want to pay close attention to them. The typeface and font you choose should complement the style of your logo.<\/p>\n<p>When choosing the textual elements of your logo, be sure to:<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-make-a-logo#how-to-make-a-logo-section2-step5","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-choose-the-font-288x288-20210816.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p><em>Do thorough research and planning.<\/em> Look at the fonts used by other brands within your industry. Can you spot any common fonts? How are the text and graphics arranged in your competitors' logos? Can you identify any popular patterns? Note your observations.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p><em>Understand how typeface affects logo style.<\/em> Serif fonts (classical letters with \"feet\") lend a timeless look to your logo; sans-serif fonts (without \"feet\") work for modern logos; script fonts resembling handwriting have an elegant flair, which is great for a vintage-style logo; and display fonts with big personalities are great for fun logos.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Feel free to combine fonts, but do not use more than two different fonts within the same logo.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>See our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.zarla.com\/guides\/logo-fonts\">complete guide to logo fonts<\/a> with links to downloads.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"6","name":"<p>Try an online logo maker.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>If you need to create a logo quickly, try Zarla's logo maker. This intuitive logo generator can help you create hundreds of logo designs in minutes for free.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-make-a-logo#how-to-make-a-logo-section2-step6","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-try-an-online-logo-maker-288x288-20210827.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Navigate to Zarla's <a href=\"https:\/\/www.zarla.com\/free-logo-maker\">free logo maker<\/a>.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Enter your brand name and click on \"Create Your Free Logo.\"<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Start typing an industry, then select one from the drop-down menu. Click on \"Next.\"<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Enter your slogan (optional), then click on \"Next.\"<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Click on \"Choose icons for me\" or \"Search for icons.\"<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Browse through the logo designs and click on the best one.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Customize your logo, then enter your email in the top-right corner and click on \"Download.\"<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Check your inbox and follow the prompts to access your free logo files.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"3","name":"<p>Evaluate and integrate your logo design.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Finalize your logo design.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Set your logo options side by side and evaluate the best ones. Get input from friends, colleagues, potential clients, and trusted mentors to help you make your final choice.<\/p>\n<p>The logo should be instantly recognizable and also effectively communicate your brand message. When evaluating your logo design, be sure to ask the following questions:<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-make-a-logo#how-to-make-a-logo-section3-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-finalize-your-logo-design-288x288-20210816.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Is your logo professional?<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Does it complement your brand identity?<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Will your logo give people an idea of what your business does?<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Is your logo memorable and does it stand out from competitors' logos?<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Is your logo versatile enough to be printed on all the products or materials that carry your brand name?<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Will your logo stand the test of time, or will it need a redesign later on?<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Will your target audience find the logo attractive?<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>When evaluating your logo, make sure you've avoided these <a href=\"#mistakes-to-avoid-when-designing-a-logo\">common mistakes<\/a>.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Integrate your logo.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Once you've decided on the perfect logo, you will need to integrate it into all aspects of your business. Choose the best logo variations for your business cards, package design, website, email, social media pages, company vehicle, and more.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/guides/how-to-make-a-logo#how-to-make-a-logo-section3-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.notzarla.com/images/zarla-integrate-your-logo-288x288-20210831.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Be sure to establish brand guidelines for the typography, colors, and possible color combinations of your logos before requesting any branded material.<\/p>\n"}]}]}]}</script> <div
